## External repo propagation (portfolio workflow)

When updating Cursor artifacts in external repos on disk (e.g. propagating `.cursor/rules` / `.cursor/commands` from a portfolio repo):

- Do **not** block on a dirty working tree: you may still apply and commit **only** the Cursor artifact changes.
- Stage and commit **only** the relevant paths (e.g. `.cursor/rules/**`, `.cursor/commands/**`) so you don't mix concerns.
- If there is a risk of overwriting upstream-local rule changes, snapshot the current Cursor artifacts first (append-only, dated).

